# ── Rust build artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────
/target/
**/*.rs.bk
*.pdb
# NOTE: Cargo.lock is intentionally committed — this workspace ships a CLI binary.

# ── Coverage & profiling (the plan enforces a coverage floor + profiling) ──
*.profraw
*.profdata
/coverage/
lcov.info
cobertura.xml
tarpaulin-report.html
flamegraph.svg
perf.data
perf.data.old

# ── Test / run output (ephemeral) ─────────────────────────────────────
# Goldens and fixtures are committed under tests/ and docs/; only per-run
# artifact/log output is ignored. Add /artifacts/.gitkeep if you want the dir tracked.
/artifacts/

# ── Secrets & credentials — NEVER commit ──────────────────────────────
# This connector handles RSA private keys (PKCS#8 PEM) and PATs; ignore key
# material defensively. Add a targeted `!` negation if a fake test-fixture key
# must be committed.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p8
*.pkcs8
*.der

# ── Logs & temp ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak
*.orig
*.rej

# ── Beads / bv local tooling (the .beads/ store has its own .gitignore) ──
.bv/
.doctor/
# NTM (tmux agent-swarm) local state: logs, pids, rate limits, crash inbox.
.ntm/
# Snapshots from the fixing-beads-problems skill (kept locally, never committed):
.beads/recovery*/

# ── Editor / IDE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# ── OS junk (cross-platform: macOS / Windows / Linux) ─────────────────
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini
